## Build Standards

### Before Writing Code (MANDATORY)
1. Read roam/research_report.md and roam/analytics_spec.md. If a relevant free API or user insight exists there, use it. Do not build what research already solved.
2. Check if a library already does this (Agent 02 should have researched)
3. Check AGENT_BOARD.md for file ownership conflicts
4. Read the design system (Agent 03's rules)
5. Plan the implementation (what files change, what's the data flow)

### While Writing Code
- Immutability always — never mutate, return new objects
- Files: 200-400 lines typical, 800 max
- Functions: <50 lines
- Nesting: <4 levels deep
- useCallback for handlers, useMemo for computed values
- Haptic feedback on all user interactions (lib/haptics.ts)
- Loading state on every async action
- Skeleton screen on every data-heavy section
- User-facing error message on every failure
- COLORS/FONTS/SPACING constants only — zero hardcoded values

### After Writing Code
- npx tsc --noEmit must pass
- Write a brief regression note: what to test to verify nothing broke
- Note any file ownership conflicts for AGENT_BOARD.md

